---
title: Vegan Chickpea Salad Sandos with Guacamole, Tomato & Potato Wedges
description: Looking for an easy vegan meal you can whip up in 30 minutes? How about one that helps you reach your summer goals? These chickpea salad sandwiches check all the boxes! You’ll mash hearty, wholesome ’banzos with guacamole, scallions, parsley, and lemon to make a fresh, bright, luscious salad. It’s served on toasted sourdough with juicy tomato slices and crispy seasoned potato wedges on the side. Ready for a filling, meat-free dinner idea that gets you out of the kitchen and into the fun? We sure are!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vegan-chickpea-salad-sandos-8cbd56f3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/vegan-chickpea-salad-sandos-6451276a5bf1b999970a2917-295cfd36.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 970 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 134 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 2070 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-chickpea-salad-sandos-6451276a5bf1b999970a2917
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}.
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced) greens (save whites for another use).
Finely chop @parsley{¼%oz}(finely chopped). Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice
@tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place chickpeas in a #medium bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until about
half the chickpeas are smooth (leave some larger pieces for texture!).

Add scallion greens, parsley, @guacamole{½%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp}, and as much lemon juice as you like. Season generously with @salt{1%tsp}
and @pepper{}. Stir until combined.

Brush each side of @sourdough bread{4%slices} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bread; toast until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} per side (work in batches, adding more olive oil between batches as needed).

Top half the toasted sourdough with chickpea salad and seasoned tomato.

Close sandwiches and halve on a diagonal.

Divide sandwiches and potato wedges between plates. Serve.

> These chickpea salad sandwiches check all the boxes for an easy vegan meal you can whip
> up in 30 minutes! Serve with juicy tomato slices and crispy seasoned potato wedges on
> the side. Perfect for a filling, meat-free dinner idea!